At least six persons, including threesoldiers, were reported wounded at the start of a generalstrike in Ecuador called to press the government to suspend anearthquake-related austerity programme.    The information ministry said workers had partiallycomplied with the strike. Witnesses said bus transport groundto a halt in Quito and schools were closed throughout thecountry, but banks and shops remained open.    Three soldiers on a military truck were burned by agasoline bomb, information minister Marco Lara told reuters.    In the central city of Latacunga, three workers werewounded in clashes with police, unionists and hospitalauthorities said. The strike was called for one day but couldbe extended. Reuter&#3;